text:
Week 9 roundup: Around Northeast Florida high school football 
Sat, Oct 24, 2015 @ 12:26 am 
ELSEWHERE 
Palatka (4-4, 3-1 District 5-5A) gained control in the playoff chase with a 45-21 victory over visiting Orange Park (4-4, 1-3). ... Yulee (5-3, 2-1) took command after a chaotic start to defeat Paxon (1-7, 0-3) 45-21, setting up a District 3-5A deciding clash with Ribault next week. ... Keystone Heights (6-2, 2-1) returned to District 3-4A contention with a 28-14 win over visiting Interlachen (1-7, 0-3)... Stanton (0-9, 0-4) stayed winless in a 33-0 loss to District 4-5A champion Suwannee (6-1, 4-0). ... St. Johns Country Day (2-5) used a strong first quarter to win 15-6 against visiting Christ’s Church (5-3). ... University Christian’s visit to nationally ranked Brentwood Academy, Tenn., was a rough one, with the Christians (6-2) taking a 53-6 loss. Brentwood (8-1) scored the game’s final 46 points. ... St. Joseph (8-0) relied on its defense to maintain its unbeaten mark, winning a 10-0 shutout against All Saints (1-7). ... Eagle’s View (3-5) cruised 52-0 against visiting Aucilla Christian (1-6)... Duval Charter (0-8) gave up 21 early points in a 41-14 loss to Tallahassee Leon (3-5)... Potter’s House (3-4) lost 36-26 at Hamilton County (3-6).
